<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Morphological description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
The frustule is low-cylindrical, valves are flat, 21.4-25.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diameter, central processes located on the valve ingroups, 6 marginal fultoportulae in 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. SEM (A, B and E-H) and LM (C, D) images of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city: A-D Pleurosira laevis A, C valve views with arrows shown the ocelli B girdle view E Conticribra weissflogii, valve view with arrows shown central and marginal fultoportulae F Thalassiosira incerta, valve view with arrow shown central fultoportulae G Thalassiosira faurii, valve view H Minidiscus proschkinae, valve view with arrow in the centre shown central fultoportula, and closer to the edge - rimoportula. Scale bars: 10 μm (C-G); 30 μm (A); 50 μm (B); 3 μm (H)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545736" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">4G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Planktonic and benthic in freshwater reservoirs, lakes, rivers, and fossil. Lack of information for this taxon must be noted, but it is known that this species is very sensitive to salinity (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.palaeo.2014.03.014" author="Roubeix, V" journalOrPublisher="Palaeogeography, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="104 - 112" refId="B105" refString="Roubeix, V, Chalie, F, Gasse, F, 2014. The diatom Thalassiosira faurii (Gasse) Hasle in the Ziway-Shala lakes (Ethiopia) and implications for paleoclimatic reconstructions: Case study of the Glacial-Holocene transition in East Africa. Palaeogeography, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology 402: 104 - 112, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.palaeo.2014.03.014" title="The diatom Thalassiosira faurii (Gasse) Hasle in the Ziway-Shala lakes (Ethiopia) and implications for paleoclimatic reconstructions: Case study of the Glacial-Holocene transition in East Africa." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.palaeo.2014.03.014" volume="402" year="2014">Roubeix et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Mediophyceae" family="Thalassiosiraceae" genus="Thalassiosira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Thalassiosira faurii" order="Thalassiosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="faurii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Thalassiosira faurii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gasse) Hasle occurred near Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Species composition of centric diatoms at the investigated sites near Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River in the year 2017 (2013 added for station 2)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" tableUuid="DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677">1</tableCitation>
). This taxon was registered for the Dnipro River and its reservoirs, mouth of the Danube in the Black Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Maystrova, NV" journalOrPublisher="Algologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="467 - 475" refId="B89" refString="Maystrova, NV, Genkal, SI, Scherbak, VI, Semenyuk, NE, 2007. Centrophyceae in the upper section of the Kanev water reservoirs (Ukraine). Algologia 17 (4): 467 - 475" title="Centrophyceae in the upper section of the Kanev water reservoirs (Ukraine)." volume="17" year="2007">Maystrova et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.palaeo.2014.03.014" author="Roubeix, V" journalOrPublisher="Palaeogeography, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="104 - 112" refId="B105" refString="Roubeix, V, Chalie, F, Gasse, F, 2014. The diatom Thalassiosira faurii (Gasse) Hasle in the Ziway-Shala lakes (Ethiopia) and implications for paleoclimatic reconstructions: Case study of the Glacial-Holocene transition in East Africa. Palaeogeography, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology 402: 104 - 112, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.palaeo.2014.03.014" title="The diatom Thalassiosira faurii (Gasse) Hasle in the Ziway-Shala lakes (Ethiopia) and implications for paleoclimatic reconstructions: Case study of the Glacial-Holocene transition in East Africa." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.palaeo.2014.03.014" volume="402" year="2014">Roubeix et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Worldwide distribution shows this species to occur in some European countries (Hungary, Russia), Asia (Russia), Africa (Ethiopia, Tanzania, Kenia, Kongo) (
<bibRefCitation author="Tsarenko, PM" journalOrPublisher="Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B127" refString="Tsarenko, PM, Wasser, SP, Nevo, E, 2009. Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A.R.A. Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" title="Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A. R. A." year="2009">Tsarenko et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.palaeo.2014.03.014" author="Roubeix, V" journalOrPublisher="Palaeogeography, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="104 - 112" refId="B105" refString="Roubeix, V, Chalie, F, Gasse, F, 2014. The diatom Thalassiosira faurii (Gasse) Hasle in the Ziway-Shala lakes (Ethiopia) and implications for paleoclimatic reconstructions: Case study of the Glacial-Holocene transition in East Africa. Palaeogeography, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology 402: 104 - 112, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.palaeo.2014.03.014" title="The diatom Thalassiosira faurii (Gasse) Hasle in the Ziway-Shala lakes (Ethiopia) and implications for paleoclimatic reconstructions: Case study of the Glacial-Holocene transition in East Africa." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.palaeo.2014.03.014" volume="402" year="2014">Roubeix et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Filigran, Yaroslavl" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B45" refString="Genkal, SI, Kulikovskiy, MS, Kuznetsova, IV, 2020. Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]. Filigran, Yaroslavl" title="Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]." year="2020">Genkal et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
